quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,124,"When he said to his people: "
  37,125,""
  37,126,""
  40,67,"It is He, Who has created you (Adam) from dust, then from a Nutfah [mixed semen drops of male and female sexual discharge (i.e. Adam’s offspring)] then from a clot (a piece of coagulated blood), then brings you forth as an infant, then (makes you grow) to reach the age of full strength, and afterwards to be old (men and women)- though some among you die before,- and that you reach an appointed term in order that you may understand.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.67) See the footnote of (Verse 22:5).
  40,68,"It is He Who gives life and causes death. And when He decides upon a thing He says to it only: "
  40,69,"See you not those who dispute about the Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) of Allâh? How are they turning away [from the truth, (i.e. Islâmic Monotheism to the falsehood (i.e. polytheism)]?"
  41,46,"Whosoever does righteous good deed, it is for (the benefit of) his ownself; and whosoever does evil, it is against his ownself. And your Lord is not at all unjust to (His) slaves.{1}",footnotes:1:(V.46)
  41,47,"To Him (Alone) is referred the knowledge of the Hour.{1} No fruit comes out of its sheath, nor does a female conceive nor brings forth (young), except by His Knowledge. And on the Day when He will call unto them (polytheists) (saying): ",footnotes:1:(V.47) See the footnote of (V.7:187).
  41,48,"And those whom they used to invoke before (in this world) shall disappear from them, and they will perceive that they have no place of refuge (from Allâh’s punishment).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.48) See the footnote of (V.2:165).
  42,31,"And you cannot escape from Allâh (i.e. His punishment) in the earth, and besides Allâh you have neither any Walî (guardian or a protector, helper) nor any helper."
  42,32,"And among His Signs are the ships in the sea like mountains."
  42,33,"If He wills, He causes the wind to cease, then they would become motionless on the back (of the sea). Verily, in this are signs for everyone patient and grateful."
  43,13,"In order that you may mount on their backs, and then may remember the Favour of your Lord when you mount thereon, and say: "
  43,14,"And verily, to Our Lord we indeed are to return!"
  43,15,"Yet, they assign to some of His slaves a share with Him (by pretending that He has children, and considering them as equals or co-partners in worship with Him). Verily, man is indeed a manifest ingrate!"